##############################################################################
Pre-requisites for building the controller from source
##############################################################################
Note: You can skip installation of pre-requisites if already installed.

1. Follow steps given in pre-requisites_README on kubernetes master.

2. Run below command from terminal inside the source directory to build 

	make

3. To Install run the below command
	make install 

##############################################################################
Installation of binary on kubernetes master machine
##############################################################################
Pre-requisites
Kubernetes cluster should be up and running

STEPS:
1. Create tag_prefix.conf file in k8s master machine with below json.
	{
		"trusted":<<prefix for trust tag>>
	}

2. Edit the citk8scontroller.service file as below with tag_prefix.conf file path
	
	vi /etc/systemd/system/citk8scontroller.service

	ExecStart=/opt/cit_k8s_extensions/bin/citk8scontroller-1.0-SNAPSHOT -kubeconf=/etc/kubernetes/admin.conf -trustedprefixconf=<path>/tag_prefix.conf  

2. Run below commands to enable service daemon

	systemctl daemon-reload  #(to activate newly added service)

3. Run the custom controller using below command	

	systemctl start citk8scontroller.service

4. To check status of this service run below command
	
	systemctl status citk8scontroller.service

5. To stop this service run below command
	
	systemctl stop citk8scontroller.service

